  <note line="11" original="sukhā bhaveyyātha (ka.), sukhaṃ bhaveyyātha, sukhamedheyyātha (sī. pī.),sukha medhetha (?)" reference-line="60" id="1">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">sukho bhavetha</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">sukhā bhaveyyātha</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">sukhaṃ bhaveyyātha, sukhamedheyyātha</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="pī." source="pali text society">sukhaṃ bhaveyyātha, sukhamedheyyātha</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="?" source="unknown">sukha medhetha</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>manual</type>
    <previous>; yaṃsukho bhavaṃ taṃsukhā mayaṃ, yaṃdukkho bhavaṃ taṃdukkhā mayaṃ. Disampati kho, bho, rājā jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto, ko nu kho pana bho jānāti jīvitaṃ? Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ disampatimhi raññe kālaṅkate rājakattāro bhavantaṃ reṇuṃ rajje abhisiñceyyuṃ. Sace bhavaṃ reṇu rajjaṃ labhetha, saṃvibhajetha no rajjenā’’ti. Ko nu kho, bho, añño mama vijite sukho bhavetha </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="21" original="vacananti (syā. ka.)" reference-line="62" id="2">
